The paper focuses on solving fill-in-the-blank multiple choice questions from the Visual Madlibs dataset, which involves understanding visual scenes and recognizing objects and activities within them. Therefore, computer vision (cs.CV) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also employs specialized networks for tasks such as attribute prediction and person activity classification, which fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in the form of localizing phrases from candidate answers. Finally, the paper deals with multimedia (cs.MM) in terms of combining visual and textual cues.
